headline: Boot Barn Q3 Earnings & Sales Meet Estimates, FY26 Guidance Up
summary: BOOT's Q3 sales jump 16% as same-store and e-commerce gains drive earnings per share to $2.79, prompting management to raise its fiscal 2026 outlook.

headline: Deckers’s Q4 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: Deckers’ fourth-quarter results were met with a significant positive market reaction, as sales and earnings surpassed Wall Street’s expectations. Management attributed the quarter’s performance to strong global demand for both the HOKA and UGG brands, with balanced growth across direct-to-consumer and wholesale channels. headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid DECK and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Deckers has followed the market’s trajectory closely, rising in tandem with the S&P 500 over the past six months. The stock has climbed by 5.5% to $111.69 per share while the index has gained 9.8%.
